comments.body:
@danielchen26 In the spirit of "Err on the side of clarity, even if clarity seems long-winded to you"in the [guidelines](https://julialang.github.io/Pkg.jl/dev/creating-packages/#Package-naming-guidelines-1), I would recommend renaming this not just to `OptimSPath`, but to `OptimShortestPaths`.

I would also mention that if you intend to follow [semantic versioning](https://semver.org) (which Julia encourages), a 1.0.0 version MUST specify a public API. In my mind, that usually implies a [Documenter-based](https://documenter.juliadocs.org/stable/) documentation with automatically included docstrings. I would also strongly recommend setting up CI to run the test suite automatically and to collect coverage information.

When a package is not yet ready to commit to a public API, it is often better to start with `v0.1.0` and then tag `v1.0.0` as soon as everything is settled
